  "texts": [
    "Based on a targeted experiment, our results show that LLMs do not accurately represent subpopulations, and thus cannot generally serve as in silico research subjects for survey research.",
    "At least, current models cannot do so in the classical \"zero-shot\" setting advocated by some.",
    "4 The reason, however, is not primarily social bias.",
    "Our experiment shows that current LLMs not only fail at accurately predicting human responses, but that they do so in ways that are unpredictable, as they favor different social groups from one question to another.",
    "Moreover, their answers exhibit a substantially lower variance between subpopulations than what is found in real-world human data."
  ],
